name: Time in the Inside
description:
Seventeen-year-old Jerald Doley, a.k.a J.D., enjoys a pleasurable and carefree lifestyle of a true hustler: he has the girls, the money, the drugs, the car, and the material things that any young man his age would dream of having.  However, Jerald's life in luxury ends as the results of a carefully calculated drug bust. Being a second time drug offender, Jerald has no chance of escaping the harsh penalty of such a crime. With a judge who has no tolerance for repetitive drug offenses and a knack for laying down the law as well as an amateur public defender who does not have Jerald's best interest at heart, J.D. is destined for doom.

Despite Jerald's age and his plea for mercy, Judge Steinback sentence him to Trenton State Prison for eight years with an eighty-five-percent prison term. Jerald's adolescent life ended and his journey into manhood quickly began as things take a turn for the worst while doing Time in the Inside.

name: Born with It
description: “Born with it” chronicles the journey of Ashley Walker, a young African American female born with the HIV virus; Ashley, raised by her aunt and uncle since birth returns to her birthplace as a teenager with a chance to a fresh start. No one knows she’s positive. Ashley discovers the depths of her sexuality and friendships and becomes promiscuous. Her decisions impact everyone around her and immediately lead to unexpected tragedies.
